              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="play" ></a>Parlour Players present "It Runs in the Family", 11th, 12th and 13th May at 7.30 in Sanderstead URC hall.</h3>
                <p>The next Parlour Players  production is a Ray Cooney ‘farce’, "It Runs in the Family". The story is set in a hospital and contains an assortment of characters including the hero, a Dr. David Mortimer who is just about to deliver the most important lecture of his life when he is confronted with a 19-year old who his mother, a former nurse, informs him is his illegitimate son!</p>
 
                <p>As you’d expect in a Ray Cooney play, the hapless ‘hero’ in trying to hide his past, only gets into deeper and deeper trouble.</p>
 
                <p>The play will be staged on Thursday 11th, Friday 12th and Saturday 13th May in the Sanderstead United Reformed Church Hall, Sanderstead Hill, commencing at 7.45pm not forgetting the bar is open both before curtain-up and in the interval.</p>
 
                <p>Tickets may be purchased on line - go to www.parlourplayers.co.uk and click on the ‘Ticket Source’ link. There is also the traditional box office method by ringing either 01883 381884 or 020 8657 2632.</p>
 
                <!--<p>Parlour Players performed a previous Ray Cooney play ‘Out of Order’ which received very good reviews. These may be viewed on the <%= link_to "Parlour Players website", "http://www.parlourplayers.co.uk" %>  following ‘PRODUCTIONS’, ‘Past Productions’ and ‘May 2013 – Out of Order by Ray Cooney and directed by Theo Spring’ links.</p>
                </p>-->
              </td>
              <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/parlour_players.jpg", alt: "Parlour Players logo"), "http://www.parlourplayers.co.uk/" %>
              </td>
